    Donor eligibility criteria and liver graft acceptance criteria during normothermic regional perfusion: a systematic review.
One-year graft and patient survival were 75% (66-82%) and 82% (75-88%) in uDCD and 91% (89-93%) and 93% (91-94%) in cDCD respectively. In conclusion, the currently used assessment criteria consist of macroscopic aspect and transaminase levels. The acceptance criteria should be tailored according to donor type to prevent an unacceptable PNF rate in uDCD and to increase the relatively modest Organ Utilization Rate in cDCD.
